SIMPLE: motile
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Motile
<hw>Mo"tile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Motive</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Exhibiting,
or capable of, spontaneous movement; <as>as, <ex>motile</ex> bacteria,
<ex>motile</ex> protozoa, <ex>motile</ex> cilia, <ex>motile</ex> spores,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Producing motion; <as>as, <ex>motile</ex>
powers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Motile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Motile
<hw>Mo"tile</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Psychol.)</fld> <def>A person
whose prevailing mental imagery takes the form of inner feelings of
action, such as incipient pronunciation of words, muscular innervations,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Motility</ent>⟦br⟧
